olive oil
2 potato
40 g butter
2.5 tbs milk
¼ tsp salt
1 onion
1 stalk celery
2 sprig rosemary
1 bunch thyme
2 clove garlic
1 bunch Silverbeet
1 packet tomato paste
2.5 tbs water
1 sachet beef-style stock powder
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 bag green beans
½ packet Veggie Mince

Bring a medium saucepan of salted water to
the boil. Peel and cut the potato into bite-sized
chunks. Cook the potato in the boiling water until
easily pierced with a knife, 10-15 minutes. Drain
and return to the saucepan. Add the butter, milk
and the salt, then mash with a potato masher or
fork until smooth.

While the potato is cooking, finely chop the brown
onion. Finely chop the celery, or grate if you prefer.
Pick and finely chop 1/2 the rosemary leaves. Pick
the thyme leaves. Finely chop the garlic. Roughly
chop the silverbeet leaves.
TIP: We've only used 1/2 a bunch of rosemary here
as it can be quite an overpowering flavour. Use more
or less depending on taste.

In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over
a high heat. Cook the onion and celery, stirring,
until softened, 6-7 minutes. Add the rosemary,
thyme and 2/3 of the garlic and cook, stirring, until
fragrant, 1 minute. Add the savoury veggie mince and cook,
breaking it up with a spoon, until just browned,
3-4 minutes. Reduce the heat to medium, then add
the tomato paste (see ingredients), the water and
beef-style stock powder. Stir well to combine.
Add the silverbeet and stir through until just
wilted, 2-3 minutes.

TIP: Add a dash more water if the mince looks dry!

Preheat the grill to medium-high. Transfer the
mince mixture to a baking dish and spread the
mashed potato over the top, smoothing it out with
the back of a spoon. Sprinkle over the shredded
Cheddar cheese and grill until the cheese is
melted and golden, 5-10 minutes.

While the pie is grilling, trim the baby broccoli and
halve lengthways. Wash and dry the frying pan,
then return to a medium-high heat with a drizzle
of olive oil. Cook the baby broccoli, tossing, until
tender, 5-6 minutes. Add the remaining garlic and
cook until fragrant, 1 minute. Season with salt and
pepper.

Divide the veggie mince and rosemary pie and garlicky
greens between plates.